<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="it-pron">it <strong><em>pron</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪt/    美 /ɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>它；这；那：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>指已提及的事物、动植物和婴儿等：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I bought a computer, but returned it this morning. 
我买了一台电脑，但是今天上午把它退了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What a beautiful baby — is it a boy? 
多漂亮的娃娃，是男孩吗?</p></div>

<ul>
<li>指在场的人或电话中的通话者：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Who's that?
哪位？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Hello, it's Bill speaking.
嗨，我是比尔。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>指状况、事实、建议：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He's not rich, but it doesn't matter to me.
他并不富有，但那对我来说无关紧要。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>表示时间、天气、距离等：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is the third of May today.
今天是五月三日。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I think it's going to rain.
我想天快下雨了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>How far is it from your office to the bank? 
从你办公室到银行有多远?</p></div>

<ul>
<li>作形式主语，代替不定式、动词-ing或从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Not matter where he is, it is his rule to go for a walk before breakfast.
不管在哪，他都习惯在早餐前散步。</p><footer>2012 陕西</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's no use saying any more about it.
对此再多说也无益。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is said that he's a criminal.
据说他是个罪犯。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>作形式宾语，代替不定式或从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I regard it important to finish this job on time. 
我认为按时完成这项工作很重要。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I took it for granted that you would stay with us. 
我想当然地认为你会跟我们在一起。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>构成强调句型：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is the President that Joan interviewed yesterday.
琼昨天采访的是总统。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was on Monday night that all this happened. 
所有这一切都是在周一夜里发生的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>How would you like<strong><em>_</em></strong> if you were watching your favorite TV program and someone came into the room and just shut it off without asking you?  （2015 浙江改）  </li>
<li>— Who's that at the door? 
—  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ is the milkman.   （2014 全国改）  </li>
<li>An average of just 18.75 cm of rain fell last year, making <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the driest year since California became a state in 1850.  （2014 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. it  2. It  3. it  </p></div>